text: A warm wind moves through the city like a slow, remembering animal, stirring the ordinary: a newspaper corner folding itself against the gutter, a bicycle tire humming a thin, tired song over the cobblestones, the faint metallic laughter of a distant tram. Morning light pours from between the buildings in liquid bands, pooling on a caf√© table where a woman in a blue scarf traces the rim of her cup with a calm, almost ritualistic thumb; behind her, a child ties and unties shoelaces as if negotiating the geometry of the world, and an old man in a hat folds and unfolds a map that has become, over time, less a guide and more a collection
